<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-18T06:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-18T06:24:00-05:00" n="769" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d769">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3796: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-18T13:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                        1921—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 2:09
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>490. <hi rend="italic">Izvestia</hi> August 12 carries prominent notice
                            official information Chicherin to effect American citizens may leave
                            Russia after presenting satisfactory proof citizenship to Anglo-American
                            Division Commission Foreign Affairs. Keeley<note n="10" xml:id="d769fn10">Royal R. Keeley, who entered Russia in September
                                1919 to work for the Soviet Government, was arrested in May 1920 and
                                imprisoned on the charge of sending out a false report on economic
                                conditions.</note> telegraphs expects to leave within a few
                            days.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>